G STRIX RTX2080 Super A8G GAMING",[564,574,575],{},"Network: Dual port 10G network card",[564,577,578,579],{},"Disk(s):\n",[561,580,581,584,587],{},[564,582,583],{},"1x 500GB SATA SSD",[564,585,586],{},"1x 3TB SATA HDD",[564,588,589],{},"1x 4TB SATA HDD",[564,591,592],{},"Case: be quiet! Silent Base 601 Midi-Tower",[553,594,596],{"id":595},"workstation","Workstation",[527,598,599],{},"The \"heart\" of working at home.",[561,601,602,605,608,611,613,625],{},[564,603,604],{},"CPU: AMD Ryzen 7 1800X (8c\u002F16t)",[564,606,607],{},"Memory: 32GB DDR4-2133",[564,609,610],{},"GPU: 2x Radeon RX 560 OC 4G",[564,612,575],{},[564,614,578,615],{},[561,616,617,620,622],{},[564,618,619],{},"1x 500GB NVMe SSD",[564,621,583],{},[564,623,624],{},"4x 8TB HDDs",[564,626,592],{},[628,629,630,636,639],"blockquote",{},[527,631,632],{},[633,634,635],"strong",{},"NOTE",[527,637,638],{},"For version 3, I'm planning to upgrade the workstation to have at least 64GB, and a newer, bigger AMD processor. A AMD Threadripper would be nice.\nIf it is affordable maybe even an AMD EPYC processor.",[527,640,641],{},"New GPUs and 40G network card are on the list of potential improvements for version 3. Though new GPUs and network cards will probably \"include\" a AMD Threadripper + a fitting Motherboard.",[548,643,645],{"id":644},"monitors","Monitors",[561,647,648,658],{},[564,649,650,651],{},"4x ",[652,653,657],"a",{"href":654,"rel":655},"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.lg.com\u002Fus\u002Fmonitors\u002Flg-29UM68-P-ultrawide-monitor",[656],"nofollow","LG 29UM68-P 29\" 21:9 UltraWide LED monitors",[564,659,660,661],{},"1x ",[652,662,665],{"href":663,"rel":664},"https:\u002F\u002Famazon.de\u002FGrundig-VLE-6220-Fernseher-Tuner\u002Fdp\u002FB0092K3C6I",[656],"Grundig 32 VLE 6220 BH 80 cm (32 Zoll)",[527,667,668,669,674],{},"A big shoutout to ",[652,670,673],{"href":671,"rel":672},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ricoo.eu\u002F",[656],"Ricoo Medientechnik"," as their monitor stands are awesome and not too expensive!",[527,676,677],{},"I'm using the following monitor stands from Ricoo:",[561,679,680,687,690],{},[564,681,660,682],{},[652,683,686],{"href":684,"rel":685},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ricoo.eu\u002Fen\u002Fricoo-pc-screen-led-monitor-stand-ts3511-table-mount-for-2-monitors-monitor-brackets-tft-swivel-arm-monitor-mount-pivoting-monitor-fastener-monitor-rack-monitor-arm-compatible-with-vesa-100x100\u002Fa-11189\u002F",[656],"Ricoo Monitor Stand TS3511 Table Mount for 2 Monitors (TS3011)",[564,688,689],{},"2x Ricoo Desk Monitor Mount Arm (TS3011) (not available anymore, a newer model has been released)",[564,691,660,692,697],{},[652,693,696],{"href":694,"rel":695},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ricoo.eu\u002Fmonitor-tv-tischhalterung-haeoehenverstellbar-schwenkbar-neigbar-ts9711\u002Fa-11377\u002F",[656],"Ricoo Desk Monitor Mount Arm (TS9711)",[561,698,699],{},[564,700,701],{},"Note: It almost as good as the old TS3011 model. The thing that I would have wished for is to have an additional cable channel in the lower part of the arm.",[548,703,705],{"id":704},"audio","Audio",[527,707,708],{},"Moving on to the audio equipment, I use the following pieces for audio input and output control:",[561,710,711,745],{},[564,712,713,714],{},"Input\n",[561,715,716,723,730,738],{},[564,717,718],{},[652,719,722],{"href":720,"rel":721},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fde\u002Frode_nt1a_complete_vocal_recording.htm",[656],"Rode NT1-A Complete Vocal Recording",[564,724,725],{},[652,726,729],{"href":727,"rel":728},"https:\u002F\u002Fmackie.com\u002Fproducts\u002Fprofxv3-professional-effects-mixers-usb",[656],"Mackie ProFX10v3",[564,731,732,737],{},[652,733,736],{"href":734,"rel":735},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fde\u002Fdbx_286_s.htm",[656],"DBX 286 S"," (Temporarily removed due to some audio issues)",[564,739,740],{},[652,741,744],{"href":742,"rel":743},"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.doukaudio.com\u002Fmini-21-in-12-out-35mm-stereo-audio-switcher-passive-selector-splitter-box-p0088.html",[656],"Mini 2(1)-IN-1(2)-OUT 3.5mm Stereo Audio Switcher Passive Selector Splitter Box MC102 - Nobsound",[564,746,747,748],{},"Output\n",[561,749,750],{},[564,751,752,757,758,763],{},[652,753,756],{"href":754,"rel":755},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fgb\u002Fnumark_m_4_black.htm",[656],"Numark M 4"," (The link is to the black edition, I have the grey one. I got it cheap from ",[652,759,762],{"href":760,"rel":761},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.rockshop.de\u002F",[656],"Rockshop.de",")",[527,765,766],{},"To \"blast\" music at the neighbors I have a very old 5.1 sound system, which sadly has a high level of noise when no sound is played.\nI'll probably replace the sound system with something better and check if it is worth to go for some USB sound cards.",[548,768,770],{"id":769},"chair","Chair",[527,772,773,774,779],{},"A ",[652,775,778],{"href":776,"rel":777},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.caseking.de\u002Fnoblechairs-epic-gaming-stuhl-schwarz-gold-gagc-038.html",[656],"noblechairs EPIC Gaming Stuhl - schwarz\u002Fgold"," because your arse and back will thank you for it.",[527,781,782],{},"Pretty good chair, though if you want to spend more go for a more expensive one with, e.g., \"limitless\" backrest and more features.",[522,784,786],{"id":785},"home-automation-lighting","Home Automation (+ Lighting)",[527,788,789,790,795],{},"I'm using the awesome ",[652,791,794],{"href":792,"rel":793},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.home-assistant.io\u002F",[656],"Home Assistant"," to control the lights in all rooms of my apartment.\nI also have temperature sensors and power measuring power plugs, etc to \"keep an eye\" on the apartment.",[527,797,798],{},[543,799],{"alt":800,"src":801},"Homeassistant Lighting Show Demo 1","\u002Fblog\u002F2020\u002Fmy-home-office-setup-v2\u002Fhomeassistant-lightning-show.jpg",[522,803,805],{"id":804},"network","Network",[548,807,809],{"id":808},"network-map","Network Map",[527,811,812],{},"A network map showing the cable connections between the routers, switches, clients, etc.",[527,814,815],{},[543,816],{"alt":817,"src":818},"Network Map Diagram (click image to enlarge)","\u002Fblog\u002F2020\u002Fmy-home-office-setup-v2\u002Fhomenetwork-diagram.png",[527,820,821,824],{},[633,822,823],{},"Icon\u002F Image Credits",":",[561,826,827,834,842],{},[564,828,829],{},[652,830,833],{"href":831,"rel":832},"https:\u002F\u002Fcommons.wikimedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FFile:RaspberryPi_4_Model_B.svg",[656],"\"Raspberry Pi 4 Model B\" diagram is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License by Jstrom99",[564,835,836,841],{},[652,837,840],{"href":838,"rel":839},"https:\u002F\u002Fmikrotik.com\u002F",[656],"Mikrotik Product Images\u002F Icons"," are subject to Mikrotik's copyright.",[564,843,844,845,850],{},"Other icons\u002F diagrams are from ",[652,846,849],{"href":847,"rel":848},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.yworks.com\u002Fproducts\u002Fyed",[656],"yEd Graph Editor by yworks",".",[527,852,853,854,850],{},"The Network Rack is shown in detail in the ",[652,855,857],{"href":856},"#network-rack","next section below",[548,859,861],{"id":860},"network-rack","Network Rack",[527,863,864],{},"The rack is 12 units (12U\u002F 12HE) high and 600mm in depth.",[527,866,867,868,873],{},"I have added some Noctua fans to the top\u002F \"roof\" of the track to have some air pushed into the rack. The fans are controlled by a NZXT Grid+ V3 (AC-GRDP3-M1; the ",[652,869,872],{"href":870,"rel":871},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.nzxt.com\u002F",[656],"NZXT website"," does not list it anymore..).",[527,875,876,877,882],{},"I'm a huge ",[652,878,881],{"href":879,"rel":880},"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FNeon_Genesis_Evangelion",[656],"Neon Genesis Evangelion and Evangelion Rebuilds"," fan so I put some cool stickers on the front.",[527,884,885],{},[543,886],{"alt":887,"src":888},"Network Rack Front Shot (a slightly older picture than from the front overview below)\" width=\"500px","\u002Fblog\u002F2020\u002Fmy-home-office-setup-v2\u002Fnetwork-rack-front-closed.jpg",[527,890,891],{},"The network rack provides up to 10G network and power to my PoE powered devices.",[628,893,894,898],{},[527,895,896],{},[633,897,635],{},[527,899,900],{},"Version 3 will probably have 40G network. The prices for used 40G network cards (and other equipment) are getting lower and lower every day.\nIn addition to that I want to be able to monitor the power used by the equipment, which is definitely high on the list to have for version 3.",[553,902,904],{"id":903},"rack-contents","Rack Contents",[561,906,907,914,936,943,950,957,989,997],{},[564,908,909],{},[652,910,913],{"href":911,"rel":912},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fintl\u002Fthe_t_racks_power_8_s.htm",[656],"the t.racks Power 8 S - thomann",[564,915,916,921],{},[652,917,920],{"href":918,"rel":919},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fintl\u002Fadam_hall_87551_ablage_19_1he.htm",[656],"Adam Hall 87551 Rack Tray 19\" 1HE - thomann",[561,922,923],{},[564,924,925,926,931],{},"A few ",[652,927,930],{"href":928,"rel":929},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.raspberrypi.org\u002F",[656],"Raspberry PIs",[561,932,933],{},[564,934,935],{},"Used for several tasks like Home automation, Security, Monitoring, etc.",[564,937,938],{},[652,939,942],{"href":940,"rel":941},"https:\u002F\u002Fmikrotik.com\u002Fproduct\u002Frb4011igs_rm",[656],"Mikrotik RB4011iGS+RM",[564,944,945],{},[652,946,949],{"href":947,"rel":948},"https:\u002F\u002Fmikrotik.com\u002Fproduct\u002Fcrs309_1g_8s_in",[656],"Mikrotik CRS309-1G-8S+IN",[564,951,952],{},[652,953,956],{"href":954,"rel":955},"https:\u002F\u002Fmikrotik.com\u002Fproduct\u002Fcrs112_8p_4s_in",[656],"Mikrotik CRS112-8P-4S-IN",[564,958,959,964],{},[652,960,963],{"href":961,"rel":962},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.fs.com\u002Fproducts\u002F72910.html",[656],"1U 19\" Cable Management Panel with 5 Detachable Plastic D-rings and Lacing Bar on the Blank Rackmount Fiber Patch Panel",[561,965,966,982],{},[564,967,968,973],{},[652,969,972],{"href":970,"rel":971},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.fs.com\u002Fproducts\u002F66602.html",[656],"6-Port FHD Multimedia Modular Panel with 6x Plastic Clips",[561,974,975],{},[564,976,977],{},[652,978,981],{"href":979,"rel":980},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.fs.com\u002Fde\u002Fproducts\u002F41438.html",[656],"Cat6 RJ45 (8P8C) Unshielded Coupler Keystone Insert Module",[564,983,984],{},[652,985,988],{"href":986,"rel":987},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.fs.com\u002Fde\u002Fproducts\u002F41998.html",[656],"12 port LC Duplex, 24 Fibers OM4 Multimode FHD Fiber Adapter Panel",[564,990,991,996],{},[652,992,995],{"href":993,"rel":994},"https:\u002F\u002Fopnsense.org\u002F",[656],"OPNSense"," Router\u002F Firewall",[564,998,999],{},[652,1000,1003],{"href":1001,"rel":1002},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.synology.com\u002Fen-global\u002Fcompany\u002Fnews\u002Farticle\u002FSynology_Presents_DiskStation_DS413",[656],"Synology DiskStation DS413",[527,1005,1006,1007,1012],{},"The cables are mostly from ",[652,1008,1011],{"href":1009,"rel":1010},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.fs.com\u002F",[656],"FS.COM GmbH",". The \"icing on the cake\" is that some cables are custom lengths (e.g., 0.15-0.25m) so they fit just right and not have too much cable leftover.",[527,1014,1015],{},[543,1016],{"alt":1017,"src":1018},"Network Rack Front Shot\" width=\"500px","\u002Fblog\u002F2020\u002Fmy-home-office-setup-v2\u002Fnetwork-rack-front.jpg",[553,1020,1022],{"id":1021},"opnsense-firewall-router-specs","OPNSense Firewall\u002F Router Specs",[561,1024,1025,1033,1036,1039,1041,1044,1052],{},[564,1026,1027,1028],{},"CPU: Intel Celeron G4900\n",[561,1029,1030],{},[564,1031,1032],{},"Fan: Noctua NH-L9x65 CPU-Kühler",[564,1034,1035],{},"RAM: 2x Crucial Ballistix DDR4-2666 4GB",[564,1037,1038],{},"Mainboard: Gigabyte B360N WIFI",[564,1040,575],{},[564,1042,1043],{},"PSU: Kolink SFX-350",[564,1045,1046,1047],{},"Sorage:\n",[561,1048,1049],{},[564,1050,1051],{},"1x 260GB SSD",[564,1053,1054],{},"Case: Kolink - Satellite Mini-ITX-\u002F Micro-ATX-Gehäuse - schwarz",[522,1056,1058],{"id":1057},"additional-equipment","Additional Equipment",[527,1060,1061,1062,1064],{},"From the ",[652,1063,861],{"href":856}," there is an empty \"pipe\" (German: Leerrohr) for cabling going through the wall and outside down to the basement.\nThe \"pipe\" holds fiber and coper cables inside, and \"zip tied\" to the outside of the \"pipe\" is a compressed air line to a compressor.",[527,1066,1067],{},"Having compressed air available for cleaning computers and other equipment is cool to have.",[522,1069,1071],{"id":1070},"summary","Summary",[527,1073,1074],{},"Well, what is there to say? I beefed up my setup even further to be able to achieve more and have fun getting to know the new hardware.",[527,1076,1077],{},"Have Fun!",{"title":1079,"searchDepth":1080,"depth":1080,"links":1081},"",2,[1082,1083,1090,1091,1095,1096],{"id":524,"depth":1080,"text":525},{"id":532,"depth":1080,"text":533,"children":1084},[1085,1087,1088,1089],{"id":550,"depth":1086,"text":551},3,{"id":644,"depth":1086,"text":645},{"id":704,"depth":1086,"text":705},{"id":769,"depth":1086,"text":770},{"id":785,"depth":1080,"text":786},{"id":804,"depth":1080,"text":805,"children":1092},[1093,1094],{"id":808,"depth":1086,"text":809},{"id":860,"depth":1086,"text":861},{"id":1057,"depth":1080,"text":1058},{"id":1070,"depth":1080,"text":1071},"2020-01-10T11:58:26+01:00","In this post I'm showing you my current gaming and home office setup.","md",{"src":546},{"tags":1102},[1103,1104,1105,596,805],"Home Office","Office","Computer",true,"\u002Fblog\u002F2020\u002Fmy-home-office-setup-v2",{"title":510,"description":1098},"3.blog\u002F2020\u002Fmy-home-office-setup-v2","8uLFhFDPEFxBP67MdhjMNL4PNBXqwalmEM5AYqnM5v0",[1112,1117],{"title":1113,"path":1114,"stem":1115,"description":1116,"children":-1},"FOSDEM'20 Brussels","\u002Fblog\u002F2020\u002Ffosdem20","3.blog\u002F2020\u002Ffosdem20","Some thoughts, notes, comments and pictures from the FOSDEM'20 in Brussels, Belgium.",{"title":1118,"path":1119,"stem":1120,"description":1121,"children":-1},"Rook: New Winds in the v1.1 release","\u002Fblog\u002F2020\u002Frook-new-winds-in-the-v1-1-release","3.blog\u002F2020\u002Frook-new-winds-in-the-v1-1-release","Cross post of an older post I published on The Cloud Report blog about the Rook v1.1 release.",1778085757827]